# Cross-repo sync (H5 / APP / Admin / Backend)

The Evair product is split across 4 repos that share contracts. When touching
anything listed below, check the other repos BEFORE finishing the change.

| Repo                                    | Path                                                        | Role                                |
|-----------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------|
| EvairSIM-App (this one)                 | `~/Development/EvairSIM-App`                                | Flutter native shell (iOS/Android)  |
| Evair-H5                                | `.../Cursor Codes/Evair-H5`                                 | React H5 shop (runs inside APP WebView) |
| Evair-Laravel                           | `.../Cursor Codes/Evair-Laravel`                            | PHP API + DB (source of truth)      |
| admin                                   | `.../Cursor Codes/admin`                                    | Sales / ops panel (Vue)             |

## Post-WebView-migration context

The APP is a thin native shell: most of the UI (shop, checkout, profile, etc.)
runs as H5 inside a full-screen WebView. Native code handles only bridge
features (push, deep links, native storage, platform auth). This means:

- Changes in `Evair-H5` ship to the APP automatically on H5 deploy.
- Flutter changes affect only the native bridge / shell / platform features.
- The H5 ↔ native bridge contract lives at `docs/native-bridge-api.md` and
  `lib/core/bridge/native_bridge.dart` — treat it as a hard contract.

## When to cross-check

1. **Bridge API changes** (`window.evair.*` methods, message channel shapes) —
   update `Evair-H5` callers in the same pass, usually in `hooks/` or
   `utils/nativeBridge*`.
2. **Backend API calls** in Flutter — mirror the H5 call site for the same
   endpoint; the backend is `Evair-Laravel/app/Http/Controllers/Api/**`.
3. **Shop catalogue fetch** — keep `size=5000` + supplier region code parsing
   in lockstep with H5's `services/esimApi.ts :: fetchPackagesFromBackstage`.
   If the two clients diverge on page size or filter semantics, per-country
   plan counts will differ between H5 and APP.
4. **Auth / token / user storage** — the APP writes tokens that H5 reads via
   the bridge. Schema changes affect both sides.
5. **Deep link / push / QR scan flows** — each has a native side and an H5
   side; neither alone is enough.

## Workflow

- State up-front which repos the change touches and why.
- Make edits in every affected repo in one pass.
- Validate with the APP preview: `http://localhost:3000#app-preview` exercises
  the H5 shell without the native bridge, while `flutter run -d <sim>
  --dart-define=H5_URL=http://localhost:3000` runs the real shell.
- If a change cannot be fully synced, call it out and list TODOs for the
  other repos.

## Known hot zones (regressions have happened here)

- Shop catalogue pagination + region-code parsing — must match H5.
- `window.evair.isNative` detection — H5 uses this to suppress dev-only
  banners; breaking the injection timing re-introduces them in the APP.

